.TH "vme_alloc_consistent" 9 "vme_alloc_consistent" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vme_alloc_consistent \- Allocate contiguous memory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vme_alloc_consistent
.BI "(struct vme_resource *resource "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t *dma "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "resource" 12
Pointer to VME resource.
.IP "size" 12
Size of allocation required.
.IP "dma" 12
Pointer to variable to store physical address of allocation.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a contiguous block of memory for use by the driver. This is used to
create the buffers for the slave windows.
.SH "RETURN"
Virtual address of allocation on success, NULL on failure.
